         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#chaniotisrrrs2016">
            <p>[This sarcophagus belongs to Philippos --- of] Agathangelis, member of the tribe Hadrianis, in which will be buried the aforementioned Philippos and Zenas, 
               slave of Aurelius Chrysippos, son of Antigonos, the natural son of [Philippos?]. No other person will have the authorization to 
               [place or to remove someone or he will have to pay a fine of -- denarii, of which one third?] will belong to the prosecutor, and nonetheless 
               what I have ordered will remain valid. A copy of this inscription was deposited in the registry-office during the fourth stephanephorate of Hypsikles, 
               son of Hypsikles, son of Hypsikles, son of Menandros, in the month Dios.</p>
         </div>
